AGI -&nbsp;Celebriamo il primo Maggio "in the only way we know: giving concrete answers to the Italians and in particular to those Italians who wear their sleeves every day and with their work contribute to the richness of our nation". Giorgia Meloni, President of the Council, told him in a live on social media at the Workers' Day.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"On the front of the labour market" the government "has achieved excellent results". - he added - "The occupants grew by more than half a million, we touched the employment record, the record of female employment, the stable contracts increase, the precariousness decreases. These are data we are extremely proud of, which were greeted with satisfaction by the President of the Republic, Sergio Mattarella, who I want to thank for his very important words."
&nbsp;
With the decree launched yesterday by the Council of Ministers "we still take care of work, we do it with a package of measures that in the within of a program that is altogether worth more than 5 billion euros, wants to create new occupation, especially in the Mezzogiorno".
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"The main of these measures is the exemption from the payment of 100% of social security contributions for two years if young people are taken under 35 years who have never had contracts indefinitely, provided they are hired with a stable contract. I mean, if you hire a young man indefinitely, for two years at the state, you don't owe anything in the limit of 500 euros per month. It applies throughout Italy and in the regions of the Mezzogiorno, however, to over 35 who have been unemployed for at least 2 years", added the premier explaining that "the decontribution applies to women, it is for women regardless of age throughout the national territory with greater accessibility to the benefit for women living in the regions of the Mezzogiorno".
&nbsp;
"In the past 16 months we have also taken care of helping companies hire, because we must always remember that it is not the state to create jobs and wealth, but it is the enterprises and their workers." On a social basis, the President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, said this on the occasion of the Workers' Day. "The task of the state is to put those enterprises and those workers in the best condition to create that wealth."
