&nbsp;
"Melons? Under the name nothing", he was less than 24 hours after the secretary of the Pd Elly Schlein. Can you vote for the Europeans for yourself by writing only 'Elly'? "That is, of course - his answer to the direct question - Elly is a nickname, because I bring the names of my two grandmothers, there is on the tab. But I always did campaigns with the surname, because I was not very well known and there was always the problem of interpretation."
<div </div
&nbsp;
A long list of precedents
The choice of the FdI leader (and the opportunity for that of the opposition) has, however, illustrious and less illustrious precedents that root in the history of the vote of the Italian Republic. Perhaps the best known is tied to Marco Pannella, Marco, in fact, in the card to be placed in the urn, not Giacinto, as the analogue wanted, as it was punctually indicated for extended in the electoral lists presented by the Radicals. There are also those who, like Jas Gawronski, elected European Parliamentary and Senator from 1979 to 2009, had no way of exploiting this possibility because it was 'called' in another way than with its name and surname, although knowing that, as he himself admitted, even his friend Gianni Agnelli would have had trouble marking the preference on the card with a Viennese surname of that fact.
&nbsp;
The use of alias, so to speak, is well known then in that of Milan, where Giuseppe Sala has always been called Beppe. And sometimes it is also a forum of controversy, as happened not long ago, in 2021, when the leader of Action, Carlo Calenda, had singular tenzone with the writer Michela Murgia because of this Cecilia Frielingsdorf, whose surname was also removed from the flyers to avoid disputes from the dismissal of the cards, invalidating the vote; a cancellation that for the writer was a serious injury of equal opportunities, cancelling a female identity.
&nbsp;
In an even closer time, at the 2024 regionals in Sardinia, he held the case of Anita Sirigu, 20 years, last in the joint list of Action and + Europe in the district of Cagliari, indicated as 'Anita Sirigu known Soru'. But Soru was the surname of another candidate in Cagliari, Camilla, supported by the Pd and daughter of Renato Soru, a well-known entrepreneur and former president of Sardinia from 2004 to 2009, who at these elections was candidate president supported among others by Action and + Europe. Until Sirigu announced he wanted to retire being 'Soru' unknowingly. >
&nbsp;
Sometimes alias is more known than the real name. It is the case of Jarbas Faustino, candidate of the Republican Party at the 2011 Comunali in Naples, 91 votes despite being Canè, a very beloved Serie A player and as such indicated in the lists. Always remaining with votes in Campania and in the football field, there is also the case of Giovanni Luigi D'Avanzo, called Ronaldo, in the regionals of 2020 for Campania free in the Avellino constituency, called so precisely for the similarity with the former player of Inter. In the lists deposited for these Europeans, there is also, in the Southern constituency for the Freedom list that leads Cateno De Luca, Sergio De Caprio, said Captain, Last, many ways not to make his voters wrong; and in that of Forza Italia, Fulvio Martusciello, called Fulvio, which always offers this possibility to those who intend to choose it.
&nbsp;
Of course, the use of the nickname is very frequent especially in the municipalities, especially in the small centers, where it goes from 'called Nero', of a candidate to mayor of Rome in 2021 for the Roman historical movement, to the century Sergio Iacomoni, who in the list symbol had also inserted the head of the emperor passed to history as pyromaniac and cruel; to Massimo Ranucci, called Stromberg, in Viterbo always in the same year; and even to Laura D'Incalci, candidate in 2021, but to Como, also called Dincalci, to get safe from orthographic magazines. &nbsp;&nbsp;
